tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE enzymes_and_catalysts (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    supplier VARCHAR(100),
    quantity INT,
    expiration_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE Enzymes (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  category VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  manufacturer VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  storage_conditions TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE Catalysts (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  type VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  role TEXT,
  vendor VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE Inventory (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  item_id INT NOT NULL,
  item_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  quantity INT NOT NULL,
  unit VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  location VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE Enzymes (
  enzyme_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  enzyme_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  manufacturer VARCHAR(255),
  quantity INT
)

CREATE TABLE Catalysts (
  catalyst_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  catalyst_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  type VARCHAR(50),
  quantity INT
)

CREATE TABLE Inventory (
  inventory_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  item_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  item_type VARCHAR(50),
  quantity INT
)

CREATE TABLE Transactions (
  transaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  date TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
  type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  quantity INT,
  item_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (item_id) REFERENCES Inventory(inventory_id)
)

CREATE TABLE Enzymes (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    type VARCHAR(50),
    supplier VARCHAR(50),
    quantity INT
)

CREATE TABLE Catalysts (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    type VARCHAR(50),
    supplier VARCHAR(50),
    quantity INT
)

CREATE TABLE Orders (
    order_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    enzyme_id INT,
    catalyst_id INT,
    order_date DATE,
    quantity INT
)

CREATE TABLE Users (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(50)
)

CREATE TABLE Suppliers (
    supplier_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    location VARCHAR(50),
    contact VARCHAR(50)
)
